This paper deals with image enhancement using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a separate CNN for evaluation, which could indicate that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The datasets used in the experiments include KITTI and Cityscapes, which are commonly used in computer vision research, suggesting that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with enhancing photos taken by digital cameras, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
